window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>The groundbreaking classic, <i>Mom's House, Dad's House</i>, has become the standard for two generations of divorcing parents, and includes examples, self-tests, checklists, tools, and guidelines to help separated moms and dads with the legal, emotional, and financial issues they will encounter as they work to create happy and stable homes. </p> <p>This comprehensive guide looks anew at the needs of all family members with creative options and common-sense advice, including: </p> <p></p> <ul> <li>The map to a \"decent divorce\" and two happy homes </li> <li>Helping children of divorce with age-specific advice </li> <li>Negotiating Parental Agreements and custody arrangements </li> <li>Sidestepping destructive myths about divorce (and marriage) </li> </ul> <p></p> <p>With <i>Mom's House, Dad's House</i>, parents will learn how to help their children heal and find a sense of continuity, security, and stability throughout the divorce process and in any custody situation. </p>"; 
